We recommended and management agreed to the following:

Inventory Committee conduct the physical count of inventory items to be reported in the RPCI and PPE items in the RPCPPE to be presented by account classification;

Municipal Accountant reconcile the differences between the schedule of PPE/lapsing schedule and the financial statements to ensure accurate financial reporting;

Review the 154 JEVs made to reclassify PPE items in CY 2022, record in the journal and ledger to reflect the adjusted amounts of the affected accounts in the FS;

Separately cost each item of PPE to properly account for the item either as PPE or inventory;

Identify the specific PPE items that were listed in generic terms;

Reclassify the CIP accounts to its proper PPE account;

Transfer the completed projects or PPE under the TF to the GF at the end of the year and provide corresponding depreciation;

Prioritize the processing and transferring of the title of the parcels of land in the name of the Municipality to establish its legal ownership over said property; and

Consider the provisions of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 which provides for the guidelines and procedures in the conduct of physical count of PPE, recognition of PPE items found at station and disposition for non-existing/missing PPE items, for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances of government agencies.

